'' title=''Andrew Nacin who is one of the core developers of WordPress has published an extensive field guide for developers regarding WordPress 3.3. The guide contains links to relevant articles and discussions on the WordPress developers blog such as admin bar API changes, Javascript and editor changes, Help screen along with API changes, etc. All developers should t [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Extensive Checklist For WordPress 3.3 That All Developers Should Check</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/3EgeD6M0_0A/'' title=''WordPress 3.3 RC 2 has been released. The team feels that WordPress 3.3 is just about ready to be released, so this could very well be the last release candidate before 3.3 is officially released. If you’re a plugin or theme developer, it’s time to test your products against WordPress 3.3 before the rest of the world gets their hands on it. Andrew Nacin has  [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress 3.3 RC 2 Released</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
